Page 3 H.B. NO. SS’i
C.D. 1
1 Therefore, the purpose of this part is to appropriate
2 general funds to replenish the remaining balance of fiscal year
3 2025-2026 general fund appropriations that were redirected to
4 support Hawaii residents' food security, enabling the department
5 of human services to meet its existing obligations and avoid the
6 assessment of penalties and interest.
7 SECTION 3. There is appropriated out of the general
8 revenues of the State of Hawaii the sum of $14,248,126 or so
9 much thereof as may be necessary, for the fiscal year 2025-2026
10 to offset costs incurred by the department of human services in
11 providing emergency food assistance to Hawaii residents during
12 the federal government shutdown.
13 The sum appropriated shall be expended by the department of
14 human services for the purposes of this part.
15 PART II
16 SECTION 4. The legislature finds that recent changes to
17 policies made at the federal level will cause a significant
18 number of residents of the State to lose their health insurance
19 coverage.
20 The legislature also finds that it is important to provide
21 insurance coverage to those who lose federal coverage to ensure
2026-3509 HB2310 CDl HMSO 3
lllllllllillHIIIIIIIH

Page 4 H.B. NO. "°
h i
C.D. 1
1 these individuals can still access health care and to reduce the
2 financial strain on health care providers who might otherwise
3 provide unpaid emergency services.
4 Therefore, the purpose of this part is to provide funds to
5 supplement premium contributions due to participating health
6 plans to reduce the financial strain on health care providers
7 who might otherwise provide unpaid emergency services to
8 enrollees facing financial insecurities.
9 SECTION 5. There is appropriated out of the general
10 revenues of the State of Hawaii the sum of $16,500,000 or so
11 much thereof as may be necessary for fiscal year 2026-2027 for
12 the purposes of this part.
13 The sum appropriated shall be expended by the department of
14 human services for the purposes of this part.
15 PART III
16 SECTION 6. This Act shall take effect upon its approval;
17 provided that part II shall take effect on July 1, 2026.
